r a cigarette ignited fumes from an open can of methylated spirits. The 26-year-old was working in a shed at the back of his property in the suburb of Kaiti earlier this afternoon. He suffered burns to his right leg and arm. The Fire Service says the cigarette lit a shade cloth and a couch in the shed. They say it shows just how important it is to take care when lighting cigarettes around flammable liquids. - Newstalk ZB Smoker burned filling mower Related Tags Fires Gisborne Be part of the news. Send pics, video and tips to nzherald. Send Find Lawyers in your area Tweet IM This Share Email Print Post this story to: What are these? | Close Myspace Bebo Digg Delicious Reddit StumbleUpon National Next Article: Man jailed for using pitbull as a weapon Special Offers National, international and travel. Get the latest from Air NZ. More deals every day 5n SAMOA fm $999pp + Breakfast 5n RARO fm $999pp + Car Hire 7n FIJI fm $1199pp + Credit Make a new year’s resolution to help you protect you and your family with Public Trust, now 1st Day FREE on 5+ day car rentals 2 FREE days on 10+ day car rental Virgin Australia. Taking you to more destinations than ever before. Healthy mind, healthy body. Stay up to date with tips & tricks, and the latest healthy living news. More on nzherald.co.nz Gisborne Oil companies reassure East Coast communities on 'fracking' Fires Lucky escape after holiday explosion Fires German suspect in Hollywood arsons Gisborne Assault accused retains suppression National headlines More National headlines National headlines continued More National headlines Most Popular Community Top Stories » 1High rise brothel comes step closer 2Philanthropist to pay for 'Blanket Man' funeral 3Tragedy ends the dreams for Gremz Top Photos » 1Golden Globes' best and worst dressed 2Red carpet at the Golden Globes 32012 Golden Globe Awards Top Videos » 1Shocking discovery, tunnel under prison 2'Crew acted too late' - cruise ship survivors 3More dead aboard cruise ship Most Co